template<typename T >
void artvision_instanton::ComputeCauchyCostJacobian ( T  xp[2],
T  J[4],
const T  x[2],
T  one_over_scale2 
)
inline

Compute the Cauchy Cost Jacobian.

% xp = sqrt(log(1+(x^+y^2)*one_over_scale2))*(x/sqrt(x^2+y^2)) % yp = sqrt(log(1+(x^+y^2)*one_over_scale2))*(y/sqrt(x^2+y^2))

f = log(1+r^2*one_over_scale2)/r^2 where r2 = x^2+y^2

Then:

xp = x*sqrt(f) yp = y*sqrt(f) dxpdf = x/(2*sqrt(f)) dypdf = y/(2*sqrt(f))

and

dfdx = partials(f,x) dfdy = partials(f,y)

dxpdx = dxpdf*dfdx dxpdy = dxpdf*dfdy dypdx = dypdf*dfdx dypdy = dypdf*dfdy

J = [dxpdx dxpdy; dypdx dypdy];

Parameters
[out]xpResidual
[in]J2x2 Jacobian of residual
[in]xSource residual
[in]one_over_scale2Cauchy scale parameter

)

Take a homography and correspondences, tells you how many are LE than the threshold This function projects p into q' and measures difference between q and q' Inputs: p, q - lists of corresponding points in two different 2-D spaces.

p[2n] and p[2n+1] are the two dimensions of the nth point.
